A Night of Classical Music charity concert took place on Friday evening at the Kenya National Theatre. It featured internationally acclaimed stars; Christopher Coritsidis (violin) Jorge Viladoms (piano) and Anastasiya Roytman (soprano).Art of Music, led by founder member Elizabeth Njoroge were among the organisations and guests in attendance to support the worthy cause. Funds raised from ticket sales went towards the Art of Music initiatives working to change lives of the less fortunate.